      • preExecute

        public void preExecute(javax.jms.Session session)
                throws ComponentNotReadyException
        Description copied from interface: DataRecord2JmsMsg
        This is also initialization method, which is invoked before each separate graph run. Contrary the init() procedure here should be allocated only resources for this graph run. All here allocated resources should be released in #postExecute() method.
        Specified by:
        preExecute in interface DataRecord2JmsMsg
        Parameters:
        session - JMS session (may be used for creation of JMS messages). Each graph execution has its own session opened. So the session set in init() method is usable only during the first execution of graph instance.
        Throws:
        ComponentNotReadyException - some of the required resource is not available or other precondition is not accomplish
